attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the first pair of side bars and attaches them incorrectly. The instructor corrects the student and he attaches them correctly and places them in the table. The student grabs the second pair of side bars, attaches them and places them on the table. Then, the student grabs a couple of screws and inserts them into the first side bars. The student grabs the screwdriver, lifts the side bars and screws the screws. The student places the side bars on the table. Then, he grabs a couple of screws and inserts them into the side bars. The student lifts the side bars and screws the screws with the screwdriver. The student places the side bars on the table and moves both of them to the left. The student places the screwdriver on the table. Then, the student grabs a couple of similar half base frames and tries to attach them. The instructor corrects him and the student places one half base frame back on the table. The student grabs the correct half base frame, attaches the first base frame and places it on the table. The student attaches the second base frame and also places it on the table. The student tries to place the base frames correctly but struggles. The instructor ask him to place the base frames on the table, opposite each other, but the student does not know how to do it. The student places the base frames on the table incorrectly again. Then, the student grabs the side bars, inspecs them and tries to attach them to the base frame. The instructor asks the student to place the side bars back on the table. The student places the side bars back on the table. The instructor asks the student to place one frame base in front of the other. The student struggles for a moment but finally places the base frames correctly. The student grabs the first side bars, tries to attach them to the base frames but fails. The instructor helps the student who flips the side bars, rotates them and finally attach them correctly to tha base frames. The student grabs the second side bars, inspects them and attaches them to the base frames. Then, the student grabs a screw, inserts it into the side bars and screws it using the screwdriver. The student grabs a second screw, inserts it into the side bars and also screws it using the screwdriver. Then, the student grabs another screw, puts it on top of the screwdriver and screws it into the side bars on his right. The student grabs a fourth screw, inserts it into the side bars and also screws it using the screwdriver. The student screws the screws into the side bars on his right and then screws the screws into the side bars on his left. The student places the screwdriver on the table and inspects the side bars and base frames. The student grabs the top tray and the instructor asks him to place the bottom tray first. The student assembles the bottom tray, grabs a bracket and places it on the side bars. The student grabs a screw and tries to insert it into the bracket but fails. The student places the bracket back on the table, grabs the screw with his left hand while holding the bottom tray, and grabs again the bracket. The student inserts the screw into the bracket and places them in the side bars. The student grabs an hexagon cap nut, puts it on the screw and tightens it with his hand. The student grabs a second bracket, grabs a screw and inserts it into the bracket. The student places the bracket in the side bars, grabs an hexagon cap nut and puts it on the screw. The student tightens the hexagone cap nut with his hand and then with the wrench. Then, the student tightens the first hexagon cap nut he inserted before. The student places the wrench on the table and grabs the top tray. The instructor asks the student to place the middle tray first. The student grabs the middle tray and places the top tray back on the table. The student tries to assemble the middle tray but struggles. The student pulls up the middle tray and the assembles it correctly. Then, the student grabs the top tray and assembles it. The student grabs a bracket but the instructor asks the student to first lay down the shelf horizontally. The student places the bracket back on the table, removes the top tray and places the shelf horizontally on the table. The student pushes the middle tray, grabs the top tray and assembles it. The student grabs a bracket and places it in the side bars. He then grabs a screw and inserts it into the bracket and tray. The student grabs an hexagon cap nut, puts it on the screw and tightens it with his hand. The student grabs a second screw and an hexagon cap nut and tries to insert the screw into the tray but remembers that he has to place a bracket first. The student grabs a bracket, inserts the screw into the bracket and tries to place it in the side bars but struggles. The student adjusts the middle tray of the shelf and tries to place the bracket again but fails. The student adjusts the middle tray once more, places the bracket in the side bars and inserts the screw into the top tray. The student places the hexagon cap nut on the screw and tightens it with his hand. Then, the student grabs the wrench and tightens both hexagon cap nuts on the top tray. The student aligns the middle tray and tries to remove the top tray, but the instructor tells him not to do so. The student grabs a bracket and a screw and places the bracket in the side bars. The student inserts the screw into the bracket and tray, grabs an hexagon cap nut and struggles to put it on the screw. The student puts the hexagon cap nut on the screw and tightens it with his hand.Then, the student grabs the wrench and tightens the hexagon cap nut with it. The student grabs a second screw and the last bracket, places the bracket in the side bars and inserts the screw into the bracket and tray. Then, the student grabs an hexagon cap nut, puts it on the screw and tightens it with his hand. The student uses the wrench to tighten both hexagon cap nuts on the middle tray. The student grabs the first wheel, assembles it and tightens it using the wrench. The student grabs the second wheel, assembles it and also tightens it using the wrench. The student grabs and flips the shelf, grabs the third wheel, assembles it and tightens it using the wrench. The student grabs the fourth wheel, assembles it and tightens it using the wrench. Finally, the students lifts and places the shelf vertically on the table.
